{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WFHebWtdcwCuASWLHkqRWV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1тЖТ# Autonomous Dev Progress Log\n     2тЖТ\n     3тЖТEach entry is appended by the autonomous agent after completing work.\n     4тЖТ\n     5тЖТ---\n     6тЖТ\n     7тЖТ## 2026-03-18 тАФ Run 1\n     8тЖТ\n     9тЖТ### What was done\n    10тЖТ\n    11тЖТ**1. valueSortify тАФ Critical security fix (PR #9, merged)**\n    12тЖТ- Upgraded jspdf from v2.5.2 to v4.2.1 and jspdf-autotable from v3.8.4 to v5.0.7\n    13тЖТ- Fixed 3 vulnerabilities: prototype pollution (critical), ReDoS bypass (high), XSS via dompurify (moderate)\n    14тЖТ- Updated `ResultsPhase.jsx` to use the new `applyPlugin()` API required by jspdf-autotable v5\n    15тЖТ- Build verified, 0 vulnerabilities remaining\n    16тЖТ\n    17тЖТ**2. groceryGenius тАФ npm audit fix (PR #34, merged)**\n    18тЖТ- Applied `npm audit fix` to resolve 8 of 16 security findings (non-breaking updates)\n    19тЖТ- Fixed: undici HTTP smuggling (high), glob command injection (high), minimatch ReDoS (high), rollup path traversal (high), qs DoS, lodash prototype pollution, on-headers manipulation, brace-expansion ReDoS\n    20тЖТ- Remaining 8 moderate esbuild findings are dev-only transitive deps via drizzle-kit\n    21тЖТ\n    22тЖТ**3. job-scraper тАФ Unit test suite (PR #8, merged)**\n    23тЖТ- Added 59 unit tests using Node's built-in `node:test` runner (zero new dependencies)\n    24тЖТ- Covers all 3 ATS adapters: Greenhouse, Ashby, Lever (URL parsing, salary extraction, requirements extraction)\n    25тЖТ- Tests base adapter infrastructure: DomainRateLimiter, error classes, Zod schema validation\n    26тЖТ- Exported previously-private pure helper functions to enable direct testing\n    27тЖТ- Added `npm test` script to package.json\n    28тЖТ\n    29тЖТ### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n    30тЖТ- **pezantTools**: 6 vulnerabilities (1 high fast-xml-parser). Has open PR #23 for zip-slip security.\n    31тЖТ- **promptlibrary**: 1 moderate Next.js vulnerability. Has open PRs #8, #9.\n    32тЖТ- **waymo-sim**: Bug in `entity.py` line 123 тАФ hardcoded `0.1` divisor in waypoint interpolation P-controller instead of actual `dt`. `world.py reset()` doesn't restore entity positions.\n    33тЖТ- **activity-tracker**: Shell history `redactCommand` regex has greedy `.*` issue; config shallow copy bug.\n    34тЖТ- **runCoach**: Empty repo тАФ only README and LICENSE.\n    35тЖТ\n    36тЖТ---\n    37тЖТ\n    38тЖТ## 2026-03-18 тАФ Run 2\n    39тЖТ\n    40тЖТ### What was done\n    41тЖТ\n    42тЖТ**waymo-sim тАФ Two engine bug fixes (PR #8, merged)**\n    43тЖТ- Fixed hardcoded `0.1` divisor in `entity.py:interpolate_waypoint()` P-controller. The acceleration calculation now uses the actual `dt` parameter passed from the world engine, so NPC vehicles follow waypoints correctly at any timestep size.\n    44тЖТ- Fixed `world.py:reset()` to restore entity positions, headings, and speeds to their initial values. Previously it only cleared collision flags, leaving entities at their last simulated positions.\n    45тЖТ- Added 2 regression tests covering both bugs (28/28 tests pass).\n    46тЖТ\n    47тЖТ### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n    48тЖТ- **pezantTools**: 6 vulnerabilities (1 high fast-xml-parser). Has open PR #23 for zip-slip security.\n    49тЖТ- **promptlibrary**: 1 moderate Next.js vulnerability. Has open PRs #8, #9.\n    50тЖТ- **activity-tracker**: Shell history `redactCommand` regex has greedy `.*` issue; config shallow copy bug."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6299f222-4d85-46bc-988f-b18dcc539a25","uuid":"06ff7791-c4e9-4d00-92d1-66050efa8d12","timestamp":"2026-03-20T13:11:02.669Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"REDACTED_REPOS_ROOT/autonomousDev/logs/progress.md","content":"# Autonomous Dev Progress Log\n\nEach entry is appended by the autonomous agent after completing work.\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-18 тАФ Run 1\n\n### What was done\n\n**1. valueSortify тАФ Critical security fix (PR #9, merged)**\n- Upgraded jspdf from v2.5.2 to v4.2.1 and jspdf-autotable from v3.8.4 to v5.0.7\n- Fixed 3 vulnerabilities: prototype pollution (critical), ReDoS bypass (high), XSS via dompurify (moderate)\n- Updated `ResultsPhase.jsx` to use the new `applyPlugin()` API required by jspdf-autotable v5\n- Build verified, 0 vulnerabilities remaining\n\n**2. groceryGenius тАФ npm audit fix (PR #34, merged)**\n- Applied `npm audit fix` to resolve 8 of 16 security findings (non-breaking updates)\n- Fixed: undici HTTP smuggling (high), glob command injection (high), minimatch ReDoS (high), rollup path traversal (high), qs DoS, lodash prototype pollution, on-headers manipulation, brace-expansion ReDoS\n- Remaining 8 moderate esbuild findings are dev-only transitive deps via drizzle-kit\n\n**3. job-scraper тАФ Unit test suite (PR #8, merged)**\n- Added 59 unit tests using Node's built-in `node:test` runner (zero new dependencies)\n- Covers all 3 ATS adapters: Greenhouse, Ashby, Lever (URL parsing, salary extraction, requirements extraction)\n- Tests base adapter infrastructure: DomainRateLimiter, error classes, Zod schema validation\n- Exported previously-private pure helper functions to enable direct testing\n- Added `npm test` script to package.json\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **pezantTools**: 6 vulnerabilities (1 high fast-xml-parser). Has open PR #23 for zip-slip security.\n- **promptlibrary**: 1 moderate Next.js vulnerability. Has open PRs #8, #9.\n- **waymo-sim**: Bug in `entity.py` line 123 тАФ hardcoded `0.1` divisor in waypoint interpolation P-controller instead of actual `dt`. `world.py reset()` doesn't restore entity positions.\n- **activity-tracker**: Shell history `redactCommand` regex has greedy `.*` issue; config shallow copy bug.\n- **runCoach**: Empty repo тАФ only README and LICENSE.\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-18 тАФ Run 2\n\n### What was done\n\n**waymo-sim тАФ Two engine bug fixes (PR #8, merged)**\n- Fixed hardcoded `0.1` divisor in `entity.py:interpolate_waypoint()` P-controller. The acceleration calculation now uses the actual `dt` parameter passed from the world engine, so NPC vehicles follow waypoints correctly at any timestep size.\n- Fixed `world.py:reset()` to restore entity positions, headings, and speeds to their initial values. Previously it only cleared collision flags, leaving entities at their last simulated positions.\n- Added 2 regression tests covering both bugs (28/28 tests pass).\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **pezantTools**: 6 vulnerabilities (1 high fast-xml-parser). Has open PR #23 for zip-slip security.\n- **promptlibrary**: 1 moderate Next.js vulnerability. Has open PRs #8, #9.\n- **activity-tracker**: Shell history `redactCommand` regex has greedy `.*` issue; config shallow copy bug.","numLines":50,"startLine":1,"totalLines":1087}}}
